Description: Rim sherd of pottery dish with flat rim; spool-shaped attachment on outside for decoration; spool painted red; also worn painted decoration on top of rim, much worn, alternating red crossed square and dark maeander?
Curator's comments: Could belong to the same dish as 1965,0930.188.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.314)
